### Central Thesis
Jerry Seinfeld's Enneagram 5w6 explains both his obsessive solo craftsmanship and his recent public turbulence — the performance is the byproduct of a craftsman who would rather be alone with a yellow legal pad.

### Changes Made (2 total)

**Transition Fixes (2):**

- **Section 5 → 6** (Writers' room → Will not stop writing): Added "The show ended in 1998. The writing did not." Resolves the apparent contradiction between section 5's closing line ("the work was done") and section 6's premise ("he will not stop writing"). Two short declaratives matching the piece's existing cadence.

- **Section 7 → 8** (Walked off-script → At home): Added "None of that crossed into the house." Bridges the public 2024 turbulence to the steady private home life that section 8 will describe. Sets up the public/private framing in the existing next sentence so it no longer reads as half-false after section 7.

